This October, Dr. C Family Dentistry held our first Give a Smile Day in the Spokane Valley. Our staff, Spokane Valley dentists, local hygienists and dental assistants volunteered their time to see patients on a first come first served basis. Thank you to everyone who came out and volunteered for our community!.

Groups, non-profits, social services can spread the word to lots of people at zero cost. It is a single point community resource where you can network with people very near you, find the resources that you need in your own backyard and get involved.   It is a safe place to connect locally.  Neighbors can come and share crime or suspicious activities, community events, resources, neighborhood concerns, ideas, solutions, recipes or anything else to help each other grow and strengthen community life. ToolzDO offers a replica of your real local community by unifying various elements of community life and activities to create a multi-use destination while empowering neighbors to connect, interact with each other, and be more engaged in their community.  ToolzDO has something for everyone - individuals, groups, local merchants, causes, local government, social services, students and churches.  ToolzDO fosters and facilitates neighborliness, simple and green living, local economies and giving of time, talent and treasures.   ToolzDO was founded on the premise that the ultimate tool ever created is the Human Wheel.  Getting to know each other and understanding of differences strengthen community living and stronger local communities make a better world.  "Toolz DO GOOD in their community". ToolzDO is not just a website but a movement to reconnect neighbors to live cooperatively once again.  Cooperation is green, builds community, saves resources, and saves money.
